Not less than three days after the kidnap of 32 passengers from a train station in Igueben, Edo state, another victim said to be a woman has been reportedly rescued by security agencies combing the area. Although the identity of the woman and the details of how she gained her freedom remain unclear, the police confirmed her release. READ MORE: Edo Train Kidnap: Abductors Demand 20m Ransom Per Head When contacted, the Police Public Relations Officer, Edo State Police Command, DSP Chidi Nwabuzor  “A yes a woman has been rescued making it a total of seven persons that have been rescued so far”, he said